THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The board of county commissioners of each county whose
4 population is 700,000 or more shall establish homeless outreach
5 teams.
6 2. Each homeless outreach team shall:
7 (a) Provide support to homeless persons near schools, parks
8 and senior housing in areas of the county in which pervasive
9 poverty, unemployment or economic distress exist.
10 (b) Develop a plan in collaboration with and request assistance
11 from the regional transportation commission for outreach and
12 clean-ups related to homeless persons for public highways or
13 public rights-of-way located in areas of the county in which
14 pervasive poverty, unemployment or economic distress exist.
15 (c) Collaborate and consult with the Nevada Interagency
16 Advisory Council on Homelessness to Housing created by
17 NRS 232.4981.
18 3. As used in this section, “public highway” has the meaning
19 ascribed to it in NRS 277A.110.
20 Sec. 2. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
21 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
22 provisions of this act.
